WEBVTT

1
00:00:10.010 --> 00:00:11.094
[scribbling]

2
00:00:12.971 --> 00:00:14.639
[scribbling]

3
00:00:17.017 --> 00:00:18.059
[hip-hop music playing]

4
00:00:18.143 --> 00:00:19.894
[announcer] And Marcus goes to the line.

5
00:00:19.978 --> 00:00:21.563
LA is up big here in the fourth.

6
00:00:21.646 --> 00:00:22.480
[whistle blows]

7
00:00:22.564 --> 00:00:26.401
[announcer] Marcus Winfield going
to the line to shoot two free throws.

8
00:00:26.484 --> 00:00:27.902
-Congrats.
-For what?

9
00:00:27.986 --> 00:00:30.071
Um. the team you built is up 20 points

10
00:00:30.155 --> 00:00:33.158
and is about to clinch
home-court advantage in the playoffs.

11
00:00:34.909 --> 00:00:36.036
[basket swooshes. bell dings]

12
00:00:36.119 --> 00:00:38.747
[announcer] Winfield going to the line
for one free throw.

13
00:00:38.830 --> 00:00:41.458
-[cement thuds]
-[crowd gasps]

14
00:00:44.753 --> 00:00:45.712
That's not good.

15
00:00:45.795 --> 00:00:47.088
[Isla exhales deeply]

16
00:00:47.172 --> 00:00:48.298
[crowd clamoring]

17
00:00:48.381 --> 00:00:49.758
-You know what?
-[softly] What the…?

18
00:00:49.841 --> 00:00:53.261
Home court is overrated.
Maybe we'll just play away games.

19
00:00:53.344 --> 00:00:54.637
[hip-hop music playing]

20
00:00:54.721 --> 00:00:55.722
♪ It's live ♪

21
00:00:55.805 --> 00:00:57.474
♪ I got a plan
Get with me in the ride and ♪

22
00:00:57.557 --> 00:01:00.143
-♪ Inside ♪
-♪ I'll make it so my… is never dying ♪

23
00:01:00.226 --> 00:01:02.228
I don't know why my life was spared.

24
00:01:02.729 --> 00:01:04.439
but I know
everything happens for a reason.

25
00:01:04.522 --> 00:01:07.025
And now. I have a new way to motivate.

26
00:01:07.108 --> 00:01:08.735
Motivate Sports Goo.

27
00:01:08.818 --> 00:01:12.614
All the vitamins and nutrients you need
in one convenient glob of goo.

28
00:01:12.697 --> 00:01:14.199
Now that's a seamless collab.

29
00:01:14.282 --> 00:01:15.992
Look. I'm glad Marcus is alive.

30
00:01:16.076 --> 00:01:18.578
but I wanna talk
about the person everyone wants dead.

31
00:01:18.661 --> 00:01:20.080
-[gasps]
-Isla Gordon.

32
00:01:20.163 --> 00:01:21.581
Who's leaking these pictures of me?

33
00:01:21.664 --> 00:01:24.709
Ali. you have got to release a statement
that these are AI.

34
00:01:24.793 --> 00:01:26.044
[Sean] How'd it come to this?

35
00:01:26.127 --> 00:01:28.463
When we return.
the boys and I are gonna debate.

36
00:01:28.546 --> 00:01:31.883
Is Isla Gordon bad with money.
incompetent.

37
00:01:31.966 --> 00:01:34.135
or I'm hearing
might be a drinking problem.

38
00:01:34.219 --> 00:01:35.053
Okay.

39
00:01:35.136 --> 00:01:37.305
You know. we could've had a new arena
five years ago.

40
00:01:37.388 --> 00:01:40.642
but Cam blew off the meeting.
and now I have to fix it?

41
00:01:40.725 --> 00:01:42.811
Look. it's just an estimate.
Don't be mad at me.

42
00:01:42.894 --> 00:01:44.896
[tense music playing]

43
00:01:46.731 --> 00:01:49.150
What? It's just a little square.

44
00:01:49.234 --> 00:01:51.820
Apparently. all the squares are connected.
I don't know how roofs work.

45
00:01:51.903 --> 00:01:53.613
It's a lot. but we'll figure it out.

46
00:01:53.696 --> 00:01:55.448
Also. the court was damaged too.

47
00:01:56.825 --> 00:01:57.826
Come on.

48
00:01:57.909 --> 00:02:00.870
That angry vein is on your forehead.
so I won't tell you about the electric.

49
00:02:00.954 --> 00:02:03.414
It was only a matter of time
until something like this happened.

50
00:02:03.498 --> 00:02:07.335
Our HVAC is 20 years old.
and our Jumbotron is made by Samsay.

51
00:02:07.418 --> 00:02:11.381
We're one of the premier sports franchises
in the country. This is very embarrassing.

52
00:02:11.464 --> 00:02:12.966
I know. but the fact of the matter is.

53
00:02:13.049 --> 00:02:17.053
we don't have the money
to deal with this right now. We are poor.

54
00:02:17.137 --> 00:02:18.847
I don't think you guys know
what poor means.

55
00:02:18.930 --> 00:02:21.558
No. it's a different kind of poor. Jackie.
We're cash poor.

56
00:02:21.641 --> 00:02:24.978
Every other owner in the league got rich
in tech or oil or predatory loans.

57
00:02:25.061 --> 00:02:27.689
Owning sports teams is
just a fun side hobby.

58
00:02:27.772 --> 00:02:29.941
but for us. this is all we got.

59
00:02:30.024 --> 00:02:33.444
I had no idea. I'm gonna sponsor
the Coffee Bean run tomorrow.

60
00:02:33.528 --> 00:02:36.156
-No. Jackie. it's not…
-Ice-blended horchata. cinnamon sprinks.

61
00:02:36.239 --> 00:02:38.700
It's been a very expensive year
with the new Dyson deal

62
00:02:38.783 --> 00:02:41.703
and trading for Tommy.
and then had to shell out half a mil

63
00:02:41.786 --> 00:02:44.706
to that one fan who keeps hitting
the half-court jackpot shot.

64
00:02:44.789 --> 00:02:46.124
Yeah. Jimmy Saldano?

65
00:02:46.207 --> 00:02:48.710
I played with him in college.
That guy's lights out.

66
00:02:48.793 --> 00:02:50.295
Stop fucking inviting him to games.

67
00:02:50.378 --> 00:02:52.505
The discretionary fund won't cover
the repairs.

68
00:02:52.589 --> 00:02:56.176
and our bank says we are over-leveraged
and that we can't get another loan.

69
00:02:56.259 --> 00:02:59.470
And the league's saying we have to play
all away games until everything's fixed.

70
00:02:59.554 --> 00:03:01.639
We have to play home games
during the playoffs.

71
00:03:01.723 --> 00:03:03.683
Where will we get the money
for this repair?

72
00:03:03.766 --> 00:03:06.519
What about Al Fleischman?
Guy owes me. I got him new seats.

73
00:03:06.603 --> 00:03:09.647
-Yeah. why'd you do that?
-Because of a situation exactly like this.

74
00:03:09.731 --> 00:03:11.774
It's always good
to have a rich guy that owes you.

75
00:03:11.858 --> 00:03:13.902
-I agree. Great idea. Cam.
-[Cam] Thanks.

76
00:03:13.985 --> 00:03:17.405
I mean. is it a great idea?
I don't wanna be in debt to Al Fleischman.

77
00:03:17.488 --> 00:03:20.450
-So do you have a better plan?
-I will. Soon.

78
00:03:20.533 --> 00:03:23.620
Because I'm great at landing sponsorships.
so meeting adjourned.

79
00:03:24.996 --> 00:03:26.998
[pop music playing]

80
00:03:31.044 --> 00:03:32.420
So who are you gonna call?

81
00:03:32.503 --> 00:03:33.463
I don't know.

82
00:03:34.005 --> 00:03:36.883
We are not going
to The Toilet King of Orange County.

83
00:03:36.966 --> 00:03:38.176
[softly] He's so gross.

84
00:03:38.259 --> 00:03:41.846
Look. Al. this is the best way
to show the board that you got the funds.

85
00:03:41.930 --> 00:03:44.641
We get this done.
you're a major player around here.

86
00:03:45.225 --> 00:03:48.519
Yeah. look. maybe we let you take a layup
like Drake did.

87
00:03:48.603 --> 00:03:49.771
-[chuckles]
-[knocking on door]

88
00:03:49.854 --> 00:03:51.606
Oh shit. Uh. I gotta go.

89
00:03:52.815 --> 00:03:53.942
[inhales]

90
00:03:55.985 --> 00:03:57.487
Come in. Come in.

91
00:03:57.570 --> 00:03:58.404
[door thuds]

92
00:03:59.072 --> 00:04:00.782
[blows. coughs]

93
00:04:00.865 --> 00:04:03.201
Hey. new office looking good.

94
00:04:03.284 --> 00:04:06.120
Yeah. they just repurposed
an old janitor's closet.

95
00:04:06.204 --> 00:04:07.121
And that fucking thing.

96
00:04:07.205 --> 00:04:09.999
I gotta roll that out every night.
and they keep rolling it back in here.

97
00:04:10.083 --> 00:04:11.459
Do you want me to talk to Esteban?

98
00:04:11.542 --> 00:04:13.544
No. no. no. no.
That's not why I brought you in here.

99
00:04:13.628 --> 00:04:14.754
Yeah. yeah. have a seat. man.

100
00:04:15.713 --> 00:04:18.591
Listen. Jackie. I'm realizing that
I've been back a while now.

101
00:04:18.675 --> 00:04:21.177
and you and I have never really had
a chance to connect.

102
00:04:21.261 --> 00:04:22.470
It kinda bums me out.

103
00:04:22.553 --> 00:04:24.555
-It does?
-Yeah. of course it does.

104
00:04:24.639 --> 00:04:27.433
And look. it's not lost on me.
You're the only one that got Dad's name.

105
00:04:27.517 --> 00:04:29.352
It means he really saw
something special in you.

106
00:04:29.435 --> 00:04:31.104
Ah. he left way before I was born.

107
00:04:31.187 --> 00:04:35.108
-But also. he still gave you his name.
-My mom named me that.

108
00:04:35.191 --> 00:04:37.902
I'm just trying to make a point. you know.
that we don't hang out much.

109
00:04:37.986 --> 00:04:39.737
We should get to know each other.

110
00:04:39.821 --> 00:04:41.322
How's your girlfriend? Sammy?

111
00:04:41.406 --> 00:04:44.867
Oh. Sofia. she's good. She's doing
an internship in Washington. D.C.

112
00:04:44.951 --> 00:04:47.078
She just sent me a picture
of her and Wolf Blitzer.

113
00:04:47.161 --> 00:04:50.540
That's okay. I don't need to see that.
So what are you doing on Saturday?

114
00:04:50.623 --> 00:04:52.208
I'm going to my local AMC.

115
00:04:52.292 --> 00:04:53.376
It's supposed to be hot out…

116
00:04:53.459 --> 00:04:55.378
-Oh.
-…and they have the best air conditioning.

117
00:04:55.461 --> 00:04:56.713
Better than Target.

118
00:04:56.796 --> 00:04:59.173
which I also have to go to
to get cat litter.

119
00:04:59.257 --> 00:05:00.925
Mom's cat has webbed toes. and it helps...

120
00:05:01.009 --> 00:05:04.554
Okay. stop. stop. stop. stop.
because that… that sounds terrible.

121
00:05:05.138 --> 00:05:06.639
Why don't you come to my house?

122
00:05:06.723 --> 00:05:08.975
Me. you. Lizzy. the kids.
we grill up some steaks?

123
00:05:09.058 --> 00:05:12.228
I love grilling. I… I make turkey burgers
in my George Foreman all the time.

124
00:05:12.312 --> 00:05:14.063
-What?
-Oh. do… do you want me to bring it?

125
00:05:14.147 --> 00:05:16.316
No. you don't need to bring it.
Just… just come on by.

126
00:05:16.399 --> 00:05:18.318
-I can't wait to get to know you.
-Me too.

127
00:05:18.401 --> 00:05:20.945
-All right. I do too.
-I think it'll be good for us to bond.

128
00:05:21.029 --> 00:05:22.280
-Right.
-Yeah.

129
00:05:23.781 --> 00:05:24.657
Well…

130
00:05:25.158 --> 00:05:26.951
Listen. that phone's gonna ring
any second.

131
00:05:27.035 --> 00:05:28.286
and I'm gonna have to answer it.

132
00:05:28.369 --> 00:05:30.788
so that means you're gonna
have to get out of here. [laughs]

133
00:05:31.831 --> 00:05:33.875
Do you think something's up with Cam?

134
00:05:34.375 --> 00:05:38.588
Like. if Cam gave Al courtside seats.
he's getting something in return.

135
00:05:38.671 --> 00:05:40.340
-Like what?
-I don't know.

136
00:05:40.423 --> 00:05:42.258
But Cam doesn't do anything
just to be nice.

137
00:05:42.342 --> 00:05:43.301
Never?

138
00:05:43.384 --> 00:05:46.429
Remember when he got Joe Francis to delete
that video of you on Bourbon Street?

139
00:05:46.512 --> 00:05:47.513
Wait. what was it called?

140
00:05:47.597 --> 00:05:48.973
It was called Spring Break Sluts.

141
00:05:49.057 --> 00:05:52.143
and for the whole summer.
I had to be his designated driver.

142
00:05:52.226 --> 00:05:55.521
Uh. I remember having to drive
both your drunk asses around.

143
00:05:55.605 --> 00:05:57.023
See. he used you too.

144
00:05:58.191 --> 00:06:01.444
Are you sure you're not mad at Cam because
he's the reason the arena's falling apart?

145
00:06:01.527 --> 00:06:03.821
No. I can be mad at my brother
for multiple things.

146
00:06:03.905 --> 00:06:07.742
I just… I need time to figure out
how to pay for these repairs.

147
00:06:08.534 --> 00:06:09.619
Jackie!

148
00:06:10.661 --> 00:06:13.414
-Can you clear my schedule?
-You mean your wink-wink?

149
00:06:13.498 --> 00:06:15.166
-Hmm?
-Botox and filler.

150
00:06:15.249 --> 00:06:16.459
Oh no. God. no.

151
00:06:16.542 --> 00:06:19.045
Nurse Jamie is impossible to schedule.
Keep that.

152
00:06:19.128 --> 00:06:21.839
[pop music playing]

153
00:06:24.175 --> 00:06:25.760
[Jamie] Ooh. bad news. Isla.

154
00:06:25.843 --> 00:06:28.721
I can only give you a half dose
'cause there's a shortage on Dermesse.

155
00:06:28.805 --> 00:06:31.307
-No. no. no. I need Dermesse.
-I know.

156
00:06:31.391 --> 00:06:32.558
-It's the best.
-[Isla] Mm-hmm.

157
00:06:32.642 --> 00:06:34.143
-Oh. you know whose dad makes it?
-Mm.

158
00:06:34.227 --> 00:06:35.061
Nicole Vark.

159
00:06:35.144 --> 00:06:38.022
Nicole Vark is Vark Pharmaceuticals?

160
00:06:38.106 --> 00:06:39.232
The girl from freshman year

161
00:06:39.315 --> 00:06:41.317
who got so drunk
she fell off the Sigma Chi roof?

162
00:06:41.401 --> 00:06:43.820
Yeah. She runs the company
with her dad now.

163
00:06:44.404 --> 00:06:45.947
Wait. Ali. I've got a great idea.

164
00:06:46.030 --> 00:06:48.157
Don't get too excited
until your face settles.

165
00:06:48.241 --> 00:06:51.119
We can partner with Nicole
to pay for the repairs. She owes me.

166
00:06:51.202 --> 00:06:54.414
I'm the one who called 911
when she fell off that roof.

167
00:06:54.497 --> 00:06:55.498
Yeah. and because of you.

168
00:06:55.581 --> 00:06:57.834
they found those drugs
in her system. and she got expelled.

169
00:06:57.917 --> 00:07:01.421
-She probably hates your ass.
-I don't have very many options. do I?

170
00:07:01.504 --> 00:07:03.506
It's been 20 years. Maybe she's over it.

171
00:07:03.589 --> 00:07:05.758
[Ali] Right. because rich girls
don't hold grudges.

172
00:07:05.842 --> 00:07:08.177
[laughs] Nurse Jamie. you ready for me?

173
00:07:08.261 --> 00:07:09.595
You get Botox too?

174
00:07:09.679 --> 00:07:11.389
Yeah. I get it in my pits.

175
00:07:12.056 --> 00:07:13.307
Ugh.

176
00:07:13.391 --> 00:07:15.726
[upbeat music playing]

177
00:07:16.811 --> 00:07:18.146
[exhales deeply]

178
00:07:18.229 --> 00:07:19.063
[Sandy exhales]

179
00:07:19.147 --> 00:07:20.982
Uh. that was good stuff. bro.

180
00:07:21.482 --> 00:07:23.234
Yeah. totally. bro. There.

181
00:07:23.860 --> 00:07:24.777
[Sandy] Mm.

182
00:07:24.861 --> 00:07:27.572
-[Sandy smacks lips. exhales]
-Hey. is there a P.F. Chang's near here?

183
00:07:27.655 --> 00:07:30.700
I did a commercial for them
and get free beef and broccoli for life.

184
00:07:30.783 --> 00:07:32.702
You got paid in beef and broccoli?

185
00:07:32.785 --> 00:07:33.995
[laughing] Yeah.

186
00:07:34.495 --> 00:07:36.456
-Good. yeah.
-Do you wanna go or what?

187
00:07:36.539 --> 00:07:38.749
As much as I love dynamite shrimp.

188
00:07:38.833 --> 00:07:41.210
I don't know
if we should be seen together.

189
00:07:41.294 --> 00:07:43.546
Because I'm. like. super famous.
and you're a nobody?

190
00:07:43.629 --> 00:07:46.257
-Dude. you shouldn't feel bad about that.
-No. I don't. Um…

191
00:07:46.340 --> 00:07:48.968
I mean. I wasn't.
Now I do. Uh. but it's less that.

192
00:07:49.051 --> 00:07:50.678
It's more. you know. we work together.

193
00:07:50.761 --> 00:07:53.306
and I'm also kinda your boss
in a weird way.

194
00:07:53.389 --> 00:07:55.892
You're not my boss. but what about an NDA?

195
00:07:57.101 --> 00:07:59.979
Yes. that's a great idea.
I've never actually used an NDA.

196
00:08:00.062 --> 00:08:02.440
That'd really help me
keep a lot of secrets.

197
00:08:02.523 --> 00:08:04.942
Wonder if
my whole jazz tap class would sign one.

198
00:08:05.026 --> 00:08:06.611
That would be nice.

199
00:08:06.694 --> 00:08:08.654
-I can't do that.
-There. AirDropped.

200
00:08:09.155 --> 00:08:10.490
That's the last one I used.

201
00:08:10.573 --> 00:08:11.908
so just erase the name on there…

202
00:08:11.991 --> 00:08:13.284
-Oh. great.
-…and put yours.

203
00:08:14.952 --> 00:08:15.828
Really?

204
00:08:16.329 --> 00:08:18.372
You know he's my favorite Avenger. right?

205
00:08:18.873 --> 00:08:21.375
[pop music playing]

206
00:08:22.919 --> 00:08:23.753
[knocking on door]

207
00:08:23.836 --> 00:08:24.795
Hello.

208
00:08:24.879 --> 00:08:25.838
[woman] Isla Gordon.

209
00:08:25.922 --> 00:08:26.839
Wow.

210
00:08:27.465 --> 00:08:29.383
You look exactly the same.

211
00:08:29.467 --> 00:08:30.801
Thanks to you. Nicole.

212
00:08:31.677 --> 00:08:32.678
Hmm.

213
00:08:33.888 --> 00:08:35.097
It's been too long.

214
00:08:35.181 --> 00:08:38.643
You know. it's funny you're here. Isla.
because not a day goes by

215
00:08:38.726 --> 00:08:41.562
where I haven't thought
about how badly I want to

216
00:08:42.230 --> 00:08:43.231
thank you.

217
00:08:43.814 --> 00:08:45.441
-You do?
-Yes.

218
00:08:45.525 --> 00:08:49.445
It's because of you I was forced
to go to rehab and turn my life around.

219
00:08:49.529 --> 00:08:52.114
-Plus. it's where I met my husband.
-Well. that's just incredible.

220
00:08:52.198 --> 00:08:54.534
And makes what I'm about to ask
a lot less awkward. [laughs]

221
00:08:54.617 --> 00:08:55.535
Sit down.

222
00:08:57.453 --> 00:08:59.163
You see. under my leadership.

223
00:08:59.247 --> 00:09:04.293
the LA Waves have a rich history
of trailblazing female sponsors.

224
00:09:04.377 --> 00:09:06.546
I'm gonna stop you right there. Isla.
No need to pitch.

225
00:09:06.629 --> 00:09:09.131
I read the brief.
and I would like to sponsor your repairs.

226
00:09:09.215 --> 00:09:11.425
Really? Oh. that's amazing.

227
00:09:11.509 --> 00:09:15.429
I promise the Dermesse logo on the court
brings so much brand awareness.

228
00:09:15.513 --> 00:09:18.015
We actually need help
launching our latest product.

229
00:09:18.099 --> 00:09:20.935
It combats an affliction
that affects my husband.

230
00:09:21.018 --> 00:09:23.104
Oh no. Does he have a disease?

231
00:09:23.187 --> 00:09:24.814
In many ways. worse.

232
00:09:25.481 --> 00:09:26.566
He suffers from GERD.

233
00:09:26.649 --> 00:09:27.733
[gasps]

234
00:09:27.817 --> 00:09:30.319
Oh no.

235
00:09:30.403 --> 00:09:32.738
God. I'm sorry. [inhales]

236
00:09:34.198 --> 00:09:35.116
What's GERD?

237
00:09:35.199 --> 00:09:36.117
